name: **Fiddaun Island**
description: Fiddaun Island M355-159 Sheet 52 An undistinguished small low lying islet N of the entrance to Kinvara bay. Essentially a grassy raised gravel bank beloved only of nesting gulls in spring. Best landing in SE onto stony beach. The tidal stream emptying Kinvara Bay turns W just S of Fiddaun.
